        <h4>Wait 6 months to wash</h4>
        <p>We know that sounds extreme—but it is 
        worth the wait. Raw denim is just that: raw. 
        It hasn’t been chemically treated or distressed 
        by a machine—it’s right off the loom and indigo-dyed. 
        So you have to train your jeans and bring them up 
        to speed with your life. Let them mold and crease 
        to your body. By walking around, sitting, putting 
        your hands in your pockets, you’ll end up with naturally 
        distressed creases that fit the way you live. 
        Wash them too early, and the indigo might fade 
        too uniformly and you won’t be able to establish 
        the custom wear marks. So hang in there.
        </p>
