        <h4>The first wash</h4>
        <p><ul>
                <li>Turn your jeans inside out. 
                Soak them in cool to room temp 
                water for 45 minutes. (Bathtubs are 
                great for this.) You’ll notice some 
                of the indigo dye pulling out—this will be minimal.</li>
                <li>Turn jeans right-side-out and let air dry.</li>
                <li>Stretch out the inseam a bit while the seams are still damp.</li>
                <li>Washing by hand is always best. 
                But if a machine feels like your only 
                option, skip detergent—or at least use 
                one that doesn’t contain bleach. We 
                recommend 3×1 Denim Solution.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

